reate a modern Material Design + Bootstrap 5 application footer component named MTK-courses.

MTK-courses is created from the image that "I WILL UPLOAD"
MTK-courses will be included in main HTML file as:

<div>
    <!-- COURSES -->
    <wc-include href="/Melify/tools/webcomponents/courses/MTK-courses.html"></wc-include>
</div>

ASSUMPTIONS
- Use Bootstrap 5
- Use vanilla JavaScript only
- No frameworks
- No borders
- No rounded corners
- Subtle Material Design motion only
- MTK-courses must be fully JSON-driven
- MTK-courses must be load-order safe
- Do not use em dashes

CORE REQUIREMENTS
- Component name: MTK-courses
- Responsive across all breakpoints
- Content wrapped in a Bootstrap container (not container-fluid)
- Uses Material Design styling principles

LAYOUT
- MTK-courses has 3 columns and 3 rows (as seen in image
- Row 1 contains a title and description below the title
- Row 2 to 3 equal columns
- Row 3 has a "View all courses" centered

BEHAVIOR
- MTK-courses links must NOT navigate directly
- MTK-courses links must publish navigation events using _pubsub.js

DATA AND CONFIGURATION
- All MTK-courses content must come from JSON
- JSON file name: MTK-courses.config.js
- Data source: window.app.courses
- JSON supports:
  - brand logo
  - brand description
  - navigation groups with titles and links

FILES TO CREATE
1. MTK-courses.config.js
2. MTK-courses.html
3. MTK-courses.scss
4. MTK-courses.css (compiled from SCSS)
5. MTK-courses.js (production-ready vanilla JS)
5. MTK-courses.config.js (JSON)

JAVASCRIPT REQUIREMENTS
- Must wait for #MTK-courses to appear in the DOM before running
- Must wait for window.app.MTK-courses to exist before rendering
- Must dynamically create internal DOM structure if missing
- Must not assume script load order
- Must not throw errors if elements are missing
- Must use an IIFE to avoid polluting the global scope
- Must wire all links to _pubsub.publish(eventName)

DESIGN REFERENCE
- Use the provided image as the design source of truth
- Match spacing, hierarchy, and column balance from the image

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
- Provide complete, copy-paste-ready code
- Code must be clean, readable, and production-ready
- Do not omit error handling
- Do not hardcode text in HTML

"Learn More" button should stick to bottom of its container
